-- PetroChina’s Sichuan Refinery Preparing for Startup
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-03-09T02:32:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-09/petrochina-s-sichuan-refinery-preparing-for-trial-run-cnpc-says.html
PetroChina Co. (857) , the nation’s largest
oil company, plans to start up its refinery in southwestern
 China ’s Sichuan province, said its parent.  The refinery’s plan for trial operations was approved,
parent  China National Petroleum Corp. (CNPZ)  said in a statement on its
website today, without giving the exact date. The plant is
located in the city of Pengzhou in Sichuan.  The facility has an annual oil processing capacity of 10
million metric tons, or 200,000 barrels a day. The plant will
start operations in September this year, according to a Feb. 9
report issued by CNPC.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Winnie Zhu in Shanghai at 
